A6. Discover cryptographic implementation used offline

In this activity, I explored how cryptography is used in offline systems to protect data and ensure security without relying on internet connectivity.

1. ATM PIN verification  
I explored how ATMs use PIN codes to authenticate users. The entered PIN is processed securely and compared using cryptographic methods, ensuring that the actual PIN is not exposed.

2. Chip-based bank cards  
I observed that modern bank cards contain embedded chips. These chips use cryptographic techniques to securely process transactions and prevent card cloning or fraud.

3. Encrypted USB storage  
I explored encrypted USB drives that require a password to access stored files. The data is protected using encryption, so even if the device is lost, the information cannot be easily accessed.

Overall, this activity shows that cryptography is not only used online, but also plays an important role in securing offline systems and physical devices.
